dlinkSwSnmpMIB.name: dlinkSwSnmpMIB

revisions.description: This is the first version of the MIB file for 'SNMP' functionality.

dlinkSwSnmpMIB.contactinfo: D-Link Corporation Postal: No. 289, Sinhu 3rd Rd., Neihu District, Taipei City 114, Taiwan, R.O.C Tel: +886-2-66000123 E-mail: tsd@dlink.com.tw
dlinkSwSnmpMIB.description: This MIB module defines objects for configuring SNMP ( Simple Network Management Protocol )

dSnmpServiceEnabled.name: dSnmpServiceEnabled
dSnmpServiceEnabled.description: A Boolean value represents the SNMP server is Enabled or Disabled.

dSnmpServiceUdpPort.name: dSnmpServiceUdpPort
dSnmpServiceUdpPort.description: This object indicates the SNMP UDP port number. By default, the SNMP agent receives requests on UDP port 161.

dSnmpRspBcastRequestEnabled.name: dSnmpRspBcastRequestEnabled
dSnmpRspBcastRequestEnabled.description: A Boolean value represents whether response broadcast SNMP GetRequest packet.

dSnmpLocalEngineID.name: dSnmpLocalEngineID
dSnmpLocalEngineID.description: This object indicates the agent's local engineID value. Changing this variable will affect the value of snmpEngineID. The special value of '00 00 00 00 00'H indicates the local engineID is not specified, and snmpEngineID will be automatically created based on the device basic MAC address. The SNMP engine ID is a unique string to identify the device. The string is generated by default. Check RFC3411 for further details on the SNMP engine ID.

dSnmpTrapGlobalEnabled.name: dSnmpTrapGlobalEnabled
dSnmpTrapGlobalEnabled.description: A Boolean value to represent the global state of sending of trap packets.

dSnmpTrapGlobalNotifyEnable.name: dSnmpTrapGlobalNotifyEnable
dSnmpTrapGlobalNotifyEnable.description: This object indicates global state about whether a specified notification is enabled or not. If a bit corresponding to a notification is set to 1, then the specified notification can be generated. linkUp(0) - sending a standard linkUp notification (defined in IF-MIB). linkDown(1) - sending a standard linkDown notification (defined in IF-MIB). coldStart(2) - sending a standard coldStart notification (defined in SNMPv2-MIB). warmStart(3) - sending a standard warmStart notification (defined in SNMPv2-MIB). Note: please use snmpEnableAuthenTraps (defined in SNMPv2-MIB) to control the generation of authenticationFailure traps.

dSnmpTrapSourceIfIndex.name: dSnmpTrapSourceIfIndex
dSnmpTrapSourceIfIndex.description: The ifIndex of the interface whose IP address is used as the source IP address for outbound SNMP traps. A special value of zero indicates the source interface is not specified, the IP address of the closest interface will be used.

dSnmpTrapIfCfgTable.name: dSnmpTrapIfCfgTable
dSnmpTrapIfCfgTable.description: This table contains a list of interface-specific notification configuration.

dSnmpTrapIfCfgEntry.name: dSnmpTrapIfCfgEntry
dSnmpTrapIfCfgEntry.description: An entry manages notification on an interface.

dSnmpTrapIfSendTrapEnabled.name: dSnmpTrapIfSendTrapEnabled
dSnmpTrapIfSendTrapEnabled.description: This object indicates whether sending trap on the interface. If the state is disabled, then SNMP notification traps generated by the system are not allowed to transmit out of the port.

dSnmpCommunityTable.name: dSnmpCommunityTable
dSnmpCommunityTable.description: This table consists of a list of communities.

dSnmpCommunityEntry.name: dSnmpCommunityEntry
dSnmpCommunityEntry.description: An entry defines additional information which is not covered at snmpCommunityTable (defined in SNMP-COMMUNITY-MIB). An entry appears in this table when a community is created in snmpCommunityTable.

dSnmpCommunityName.name: dSnmpCommunityName
dSnmpCommunityName.description: This object indicates the name of the community.

dSnmpCommunityAccessListName.name: dSnmpCommunityAccessListName
dSnmpCommunityAccessListName.description: This object indicates the name of a standard access list to control the user to use this community string to access to the SNMP agent. Specify the valid user in the source address field of the access list entry. A zero length string indicates the access list is not specified.

dSnmpGroupTable.name: dSnmpGroupTable
dSnmpGroupTable.description: This table consists of a list of groups.

dSnmpGroupEntry.name: dSnmpGroupEntry
dSnmpGroupEntry.description: An entry consists of additional informaiton which is not covered at vacmAccessTable (defined in SNMP-VIEW-BASED-ACM-MIB). An entry appears in this table when a group is created in vacmAccessTable or vacmSecurityToGroupTable.

dSnmpGroupName.name: dSnmpGroupName
dSnmpGroupName.description: This object indicates the name of the group.

dSnmpGroupVersion.name: dSnmpGroupVersion
dSnmpGroupVersion.description: This object indicates the version of the entry.

dSnmpGroupAccessListName.name: dSnmpGroupAccessListName
dSnmpGroupAccessListName.description: This object indicates the name of a standard access control list (ACL) to associate with the group. A zero length string indicates the access list is not specified.

dSnmpHostTable.name: dSnmpHostTable
dSnmpHostTable.description: This table consists of a list of recipients for the SNMP notification.

dSnmpHostEntry.name: dSnmpHostEntry
dSnmpHostEntry.description: An entry consists of additional informaiton which is not covered at snmpTargetAddrTable and snmpTargetParamsTable (defined in SNMP-TARGET-MIB). An entry appears in this table when a target address is created in snmpTargetAddrTable.

dSnmpHostAddrName.name: dSnmpHostAddrName
dSnmpHostAddrName.description: This object indicates the address name of the recipients.

dSnmpHostVrfName.name: dSnmpHostVrfName
dSnmpHostVrfName.description: This object indicates the name of the routing forwarding instance. A zero length string indicates the object is not specified.

dSnmpHostUdpPort.name: dSnmpHostUdpPort
dSnmpHostUdpPort.description: This object indicates trap UDP port number.

dSnmpUserTable.name: dSnmpUserTable
dSnmpUserTable.description: This table consists of a list of recipients for the SNMP notification.

dSnmpUserEntry.name: dSnmpUserEntry
dSnmpUserEntry.description: An entry consists of additional informaiton which is not covered at usmUserTable (defined in SNMP-USER-BASED-SM-MIB). An entry appears in this table when a user is created in usmUserTable.

dSnmpUserName.name: dSnmpUserName
dSnmpUserName.description: This object indicates the name of the user.

dSnmpUserAccessListName.name: dSnmpUserAccessListName
dSnmpUserAccessListName.description: This object indicates the name of a standard IP access control list (ACL) to associate with the user. A zero length string indicates the access list is not specified.

dSnmpCompliance.name: dSnmpCompliance
dSnmpCompliance.description: The compliance statement for entities which implement the DLINKSW-SNMP-MIB.

dSnmpSysCfgGroup.name: dSnmpSysCfgGroup
dSnmpSysCfgGroup.description: A collection of objects provides the information for SNMP server.

dSnmpTrapCfgGroup.name: dSnmpTrapCfgGroup
dSnmpTrapCfgGroup.description: A collection of objects provides system-wide control of traps.

dSnmpTrapIfCfgGroup.name: dSnmpTrapIfCfgGroup
dSnmpTrapIfCfgGroup.description: A collection of objects provides interface-specific control of traps.

dSnmpCommunityExtGroup.name: dSnmpCommunityExtGroup
dSnmpCommunityExtGroup.description: The collection of objects provides configuration for community feature which extends SNMP community.

dSnmpTargetExtGroup.name: dSnmpTargetExtGroup
dSnmpTargetExtGroup.description: The collection of objects provides configuration for recipient of the SNMP notification.

dSnmpVacmExtGroup.name: dSnmpVacmExtGroup
dSnmpVacmExtGroup.description: A collection of objects providing for remote configuration of an SNMP engine which extends the SNMP VACM (View-based Access Control Model) and USM (User-based Security Model).
